title: epiphany_(holiday)
body:
[b]Epiphany[/b], also known as [b]Theophany[/b] in Eastern Christian traditions, is a Christian feast day traditionally held on January 6th. It is sometimes called [b]Three King's Day[/b] and in some traditions celebrated as [b]Little Christmas[/b].

In Western Christianity, the feast commemorates primarily the visit of the Magi (aka The Three Wise Men or Three Kings) to the baby Jesus.  In Eastern Christianity the feast commemorates the baptism of Jesus in the Jordan River.

In some countries it is celebrated on the Sunday after January 1st. In Eastern Churches that still follow the Julian calendar, they observe the feast on January 19th on the Gregorian calendar.

title: plimsoll_line
body: The [b]Plimsoll line[/b], also known as the [b]International Load Line[/b] or simply the [b]waterline[/b], is a marking on a ship's hull which indicates the vessel's draft at a range of allowable load limits. It is named for the Hon. Samuel Plimsoll MP (1824–1898), a British Member of Parliament and social reformer who was an early campaigner for the imposition of a legal requirement for merchant ships to be so marked.

title: miriam_(bloodstained)
body:
The protagonist of [[Bloodstained: Ritual of the Night]].

Picked up as an orphan by an Alchemist at a young age, she became a host for the dark Alchemists’ curse. 
Although the magi-crystals were fused with her body at a young age, for 10 years she lay sleeping while the curse matured to its full form. 
It was during this period that the demons arrived, meaning that she missed their appearance and awoke with a mild form of amnesia, not quite fully understanding what happened to her.

She is a woman of few words but strong of purpose. 
Her youth is deceiving, making her seem confrontational and quick to judge, though in reality she is constantly evaluating her next step. 
The pain she felt as an orphaned child fuels her compassionate desire to protect her loved ones and friends.

She has [[medium_hair|medium-length]] [[black hair]], [[blue eyes]], [[large breasts]], and has [[tattoo]]s all over her body as a result of the crystals infused into her body, including one on her left breast. title: timmy_burch
body:
Minor [[South Park]] character. Was intended to be a one-shot and gag character in "The Tooth Fairys Tats 2000", but would end up becoming one of the most iconic characters in the franchise.

He has [[short hair|short]] [[orange hair]] and wears a [[red sweater]]. He uses a [[wheelchair]] to move around.

title: jimmy_valmer
body:
Minor [[South Park]] character. A handicapped boy with a stutter who likes doing stand-up comedy. Was originally a one-shot character in "Cripple Fight" and not even a resident of South Park. The creators took a liking to him and integrated him further into the cast and classroom, deciding that he'd be easier to write for than [[timmy burch|Timmy]], even portraying them as best friends as opposed to their previous (one-sided) rivalry in "Cripple Fight". Nowadays, he's either hanging out as a member of Craig's Gang or with his best friend Timmy.

He has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] and wears [[braces]]. Due to his paralysis, he has [[uneven eyes]]. He wears a [[yellow shirt]] and uses [[crutch]]es to walk.

title: sin_and_punishment
body:
[i][b]Sin & Punishment[/b][/i] is series of a rail-shooters created by [[treasure_(developer)|Treasure]].

The first game in the series, [i]Sin & Punishment[/i] (subtitled [i]Successor of the Earth[/i]), debuted on the Nintendo 64 in late 2000. Treasure did plan on releasing the game overseas, but due to the Nintendo 64's lifespan was at its end, the game stayed only in Japan and ultimately became one of Treasure's most sought-after imports alongside [i][[radiant_silvergun|Radiant Silvergun]][/i]. The game uses a unique control style that allowed players to move and aim independently from other rail-shooters of its time, as well as some light platforming elements and featured many bosses to tackle. In 2007, the game was re-released on the Wii's Virtual Console overseas.

In 2009, a sequel was released for the Wii, utilizing the Wii's motion controls (while supporting traditional controllers) and gives the protagonists the ability to move more freely in the 2D plane, making it more akin to shoot 'em ups such as [i]DoDonPachi[/i] and [i]RayForce[/i]. Unlike its predecessor, the sequel was released in North America and Europe roughly a year later as [i]Sin & Punishment: Star Successor[/i] and [i]Sin & Punishment: Successor of the Skies[/i] respectively.

title: magatama
body:
A "magatama":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magatama is a curved, "comma-shaped" bead or jewel, usually worn on a necklace. Often made of jade, magatama were produced in prehistoric Japan, and are associated with ancient Japanese mythology. (Similar jewels were found in ancient Korea, where they are called "gogok":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gogok].) A famous example is the Yasakani no Magatama, one of the three [[japanese regalia|imperial regalia of Japan]]. Sometimes worn for its religious meaning, sometimes just as a fashion accessory.

title: hms_vanguard
body: The last battleship ever built by Britain. Designed as a "cheap" battleship utilizing the turrets of the Courageous-class battlecruisers when they were converted to carriers. Similar in design to the King Geroge V and the [unbuilt] Lion class battleships in many ways. Was completed too late for the way. She was most famous to taking the then princess Elizabeth to visit South Africa in 1947. Spent most of her years in reserve before being broken up in 1960.  The idea behind of Vanguard's construction was to create a cheap, fast, fully armoured battlecruiser/fast battleship for use against Japanese heavy cruisers and modernized Kongou-class battlecruisers, for this role she would had been more than adequate but, ultimately, when compared to other last gen battleships like Richelieus or Iowas Vanguard comes off looking rather anemic in her armament.

title: hms_hood
body:
British late WWI battlecruiser, lead ship of the Admiral-class battlecruisers (although the rest of the class was canceled). For over 20 years HMS Hood was the largest warship in the world, and the pride of the British Empire. Due to her flagship duties she never got the chance to get various large scale upgrades and refits that she desperately needed to stay a relevant combat unit.  Hood's primary actions during her career were the cruise across world with HMS Repulse in 1923-1924, patrols during Spanish Civil War, taking part in the Operation Catapult (attack on Mers-el-Kebir after France had surrendered to Germans) during which she might have sunk French battleship Bretagne, and Battle of Denmark Strait which saw her rather explosive end after she and freshly commissioned battleship HMS Prince of Wales engaged German battleship Bismarck and heavy cruiser Prinz Eugen.

While popular among the British public and the symbol of British Empire during the interwar years HMS Hood was however a rather flawed ship; her hasty up-armoring after the Battle of Jutland had left her with both rather obsolete armor scheme and several thousand tons overweight, this made HMS Hood rather wet ship (especially in harsh North Atlantic waters) and during her whole career Hood was plagued with unusually high rates of tuberculosis infections among her crew when compared to other Royal Navy vessels. Hood was also the reason why during WNT Britain was only allowed to build 2 battleships with 16" guns (the ratio of post-Jutland capital ships being 3-3-2 between USA, UK, and Japan).

title: nerf_gun
body:
[b]Nerf gun[/b] describes a family of colorful [[toy_gun|toy guns]] by Hasbro which launch harmless projectiles. Usually these projectiles are foam darts with plastic tips, but new projectiles have also been developed in the shape of foam spheres. Over the years, Nerf weapons (and clones by Buzz Bee, Air Zone or Dart Zone) have been sold and enjoyed worldwide, and have taken many forms (e.g. similar to revolvers, pistols, rifles, machine guns) and load in manners similar to many real-life firearms: revolver cylinders, autoloading magazines, breech, muzzle, and ammunition belt.

Among Nerf enthusiasts, the word "gun" is often replaced with "blaster," so as to avoid confusion with firearms and association with injury or death. Also, the muzzles in particular of many Nerf blasters are painted or molded in orange to indicate a priority on safety. The official Nerf brand also produces licensed toys based on weapons from popular franchises including [[Halo (series)|]], [[Star Wars]], [[Overwatch]], [[Fortnite]], and [[Marvel]].

Use this tag when the image contains a recognizable Nerf gun model or the gun is shooting signature Nerf projectiles.

Through the use of the Metamorphosis black box, the blades on its body can be used for various close combat attacks. In this form, Mazinger gains a great increase in power, enough to destroy an entire planet. However, the pilot and robot enter a frenzied rage causing them to destroy anything in sight until nothing is left.

ZERO possesses a sentient artificial intelligence that merges with its pilot, allowing it to move without one and even have a personality. ZERO desires to be the only super robot in existence and the presence of another Mazinger is one of the things that can set it off, desiring the destruction of this obstacle above all else. Due to the link between the pilot and Z, if any of the pilots possess a state of madness ZERO will be activated.

After consuming multiple timelines, ZERO had managed to become its own independent entity no longer held back by a pilot or even a reality- Possessing enough power to influence other realities where it is the only Mazinger or super robot in all of existence. Its only special abilities in the game proper are to hover after a jump (without losing height) for an extended duration compared to other characters and to constantly float (whether standing still or moving) without losing speed or sinking when moving over water. Officially, [[Dr. Eggman]] created it with the intent that its doll-like appearance would catch [[Sonic the Hedgehog|Sonic]] off guard.

Its [[expressionless|blank expression]] and slow move speed have lent it some popularity in horror memes, including a creepypasta that claims successfully using Tails Doll to win a race against [[Super Sonic]] will cause it to attack the player in real life.

Born out of the band [[Mandrake (band)|]], and consistently headed by [[Hirasawa Susumu]], P-MODEL is an influential Japanese electronic rock band, playing from 1979 to the year 2000. title: brown_thoroughbred_(kemono_friends)
body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. One of many "Friends" in Japari Park. The Thoroughbred Trio were created for a promotion involving the Anime and the [[Japan Racing Association]]. They have since integrated with the wider franchise and the JRA moved on with [[umamusume|a different franchise]].

The Domestic Horse ([i]Equus ferus caballus[/i]) is a one-toed hoofed animal often used as a best of burden. With time, they were eventually bred for  many uses. The Thoroughbred breed is a hotblooded breed made from a mix of Arabian, Barb and Turk horses, bred specifically for speed and racing. They are the breed used in flat racing.

A "bay" horse denotes a horse with a brown coat with leg points (darker fur on the legs). A "brown" horse denotes a bay horse with a near-black coat, containing some lighter brown hairs. Not to be confused with a black horse (uniformly black aside from any potential white markings) or a dark bay horse (a darker brown with leg points but no black hair).

Brown Thoroughbred is (naturally) a [[horse girl]] with long black hair resembling a mane, wearing a black sports ensemble.
